01:01:24,514 --> 01:01:26,927
who are the real security guards
at the real El Rodeo,

852
01:01:27,017 --> 01:01:30,009
and really nice performances.

853
01:01:30,103 --> 01:01:33,186
Particularly by this guy, Cosme,
who's gonna be the guy

854
01:01:33,273 --> 01:01:34,729
on the left with the bald head.

855
01:01:34,816 --> 01:01:37,023
And most everybody in the place
are regulars.

856
01:01:37,110 --> 01:01:40,523
It's a Nortefo disco,
the people are from northern Mexico,

857
01:01:40,614 --> 01:01:44,027
the music has got
a heavy polka influence.

858
01:01:44,117 --> 01:01:46,950
And we substituted Calexico
and a couple of other bands.

859
01:01:59,758 --> 01:02:02,625
And Max doesn't know
what he's getting into.

860
01:02:07,390 --> 01:02:10,803
One of the things that intrigued me
about Stuart Beattie's script

861
01:02:10,894 --> 01:02:15,479
was the way the storylines intersect.

862
01:02:15,565 --> 01:02:18,683
They're held in a very disciplined way.

863
01:02:18,777 --> 01:02:21,189
Discrete, each in its own channel.

864
01:02:24,407 --> 01:02:27,115
And we're about to see
two of them collide,

865
01:02:27,202 --> 01:02:31,241
as the shadowy,
silhouetted figures we established

866
01:02:31,331 --> 01:02:34,073
coming into the FBI surveillance

867
01:02:34,167 --> 01:02:38,331
are, in fact,
revealed to be Fanning and Weidner,

868
01:02:38,421 --> 01:02:42,164
who have information
that is specifically, is and only is,

869
01:02:42,259 --> 01:02:44,216
that there's a linkage between victims.

870
01:02:44,302 --> 01:02:47,511
Not who the victims are
or how they network together,

871
01:02:47,597 --> 01:02:50,055
or who's responsible for killing them.

872
01:03:01,403 --> 01:03:06,113
And somebody told Pedrosa,
played by Bruce McGill,

873
01:03:06,199 --> 01:03:08,281
to cooperate with these guys
and talk to them,

874
01:03:08,368 --> 01:03:11,611
and he's totally reluctant to
and is stiffing them.

