01:03:42,485 --> 01:03:45,398
described in the alley behind Ramone's

877
01:03:46,740 --> 01:03:49,357
and launches them
on a voyage of discovery

878
01:03:49,451 --> 01:03:53,490
that's gonna result in the convergence
of these two vectors.

879
01:03:53,580 --> 01:03:55,992
And what's nice about Beattie's script
is the way,

880
01:03:56,082 --> 01:03:59,541
once we know the vectors
are going to converge, he leaps ahead,

881
01:03:59,627 --> 01:04:04,121
and the next time we go back
to the surveillance location,

882
01:04:04,215 --> 01:04:08,129
Beattie leaps ahead
to the convergence already happened

883
01:04:08,219 --> 01:04:11,337
and just takes us
right into the important part of it,

884
01:04:11,431 --> 01:04:13,422
which is the conclusion.

885
01:04:15,018 --> 01:04:18,727
And there's a great poster
for LA's famous Que Buena Radio.

886
01:04:24,611 --> 01:04:26,978
And El Rodeo on the interior is black-lit,

887
01:04:27,072 --> 01:04:30,110
and these are the actual murals
on their walls.

888
01:04:30,200 --> 01:04:33,864
And these are some
of the actual security guards there.

889
01:04:33,953 --> 01:04:37,162
A couple other of these guys
playing security guards

