01:05:11,491 --> 01:05:14,449
And the two story tracks
between the LAPD and the FBI

898
01:05:14,536 --> 01:05:17,369
have converged, and now their information

899
01:05:17,455 --> 01:05:18,450
is actually revealed to us,

900
01:05:18,540 --> 01:05:20,535
'cause we have not known,
up to this point,

901
01:05:20,625 --> 01:05:22,582
who these people are
who are being killed,

902
01:05:22,669 --> 01:05:25,036
which is very unusual
when you think about it.

903
01:05:25,130 --> 01:05:27,588
We're engaged in a picture
in which Vincent is killing people,

904
01:05:27,674 --> 01:05:32,544
and he's taken captive Max,
who's compelled to go along with him.

905
01:05:36,808 --> 01:05:39,266
And we don't know

906
01:05:39,352 --> 01:05:41,639
why the people who are being killed
are being killed.

907
01:05:41,729 --> 01:05:46,223
They're obviously crimes of dispassion.
Vincent is indifferent.

908
01:05:46,317 --> 01:05:50,561
And we're gonna discover later
that Vincent isn't even sure

909
01:05:50,655 --> 01:05:53,113
why they're being killed.

910
01:05:53,199 --> 01:05:56,317
So the way the information is marshalled,

911
01:05:56,411 --> 01:05:59,153
the way it's moved around,
and where it's revealed

912
01:05:59,247 --> 01:06:03,957
is fascinating to me, and it enhances,
for me, the sense of immediacy,

913
01:06:04,043 --> 01:06:06,375
because when you are immediately
in the moment of something,

914
01:06:06,463 --> 01:06:09,084
you don't know the back-story.
You don't know the context.

915
01:06:09,174 --> 01:06:12,633
You don't know everything
about where people came from.

916
01:06:15,221 --> 01:06:18,589
You're just occupied
with the "right now" of it.

917
01:06:18,683 --> 01:06:23,302
And that's what appealed to me
about doing this film was that,

918
01:06:23,396 --> 01:06:26,434
"Could I make a motion picture
in which I can engage the audience

919
01:06:26,524 --> 01:06:28,812
"in the 'right now' of it
without a lot of history,

920
01:06:28,902 --> 01:06:32,315
"without a lot of exposition,
so that it kind of, in a way,

921
01:06:32,405 --> 01:06:35,443
"almost simulates our experience
of the present

922
01:06:35,533 --> 01:06:37,615
"when we're put in a context
we don't know?"

923
01:06:37,702 --> 01:06:40,198
We don't know the circumstance,
we don't know exactly where we are.

924
01:06:40,288 --> 01:06:43,201
The landscape may be
somewhat foreign to us.

925
01:06:43,583 --> 01:06:47,326
And so we have less answers
than we have answers.

